    "mechanism": "A calibration group provides baseline estimates of uncertain quantities. Subjects in the treatment condition first judge whether a fixed anchor value is higher or lower than the true value, then estimate each quantity. Anchors are set at predetermined percentiles of the calibration group's distribution. Anchored estimates are transformed into percentiles relative to the calibration group's empirical quantiles. This enables standardized pooling across problems and computation of effect magnitude. The method quantifies how the anchor influences the final estimate magnitude relative to baseline.",
