    "mechanism": "Participants are presented with statements, scenarios, and verbal texts coded for mentions of five moral foundation dimensions: Harm/care, Fairness/reciprocity, Ingroup/loyalty, Authority/respect, Purity/sanctity. For each stimulus, responses are recorded as endorsement/agreement scores or word-frequency counts depending on the modality (explicit questionnaire, implicit judgment, or text corpus). Responses are aggregated across foundation dimensions. Foundation endorsement profiles are compared across participants stratified by political ideology. The computational task is quantifying and comparing the relative weights of five foundation dimensions in judgment or text.",
